name: North Tripyramid

trails_config.name: North Slide & South Slide Loop
trails_config.description: A challenging loop for adventurous hikers: follow Livermore Trail to the base of North Tripyramid’s infamous North Slide, a steep scramble up exposed open rock that tests your nerve (not safe when wet). After summiting North Tripyramid, traverse to Middle Tripyramid and descend via the loose gravelly South Slide. This loop provides an adrenaline rush and unique views from the slide, truly earning its place among the Terrifying 25.

current_conditions.ai_summary: A spectacular hike located in New Hampshire. Standing at 4180 feet, North Tripyramid offers breathtaking views and a rewarding challenge for hikers of all levels.
risk_factors: Check local trail conditions before departing.
Start early to avoid afternoon storms.

generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 4180 feet, North Tripyramid is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its approachable and scenic terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **North Slide & South Slide Loop**, a **9.6 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **Middle Tripyramid**, which is just 0.7 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
